    region orientation (
        name: Orientation
        type: staticContent
        source {
            htmlCode:
                ```html
                <p class="col-8">
                    The <strong>orientation</strong> attribute determines your PWA's preferred launch layout. Possible choices are:
                </p>
                
                <ul>
                    <li>Any</li>
                    <li>Natural</li>
                    <li>Landscape</li>
                    <li>Landscape Secondary</li>
                    <li>Portrait</li>
                    <li>Landscape Primary</li>
                    <li>Portrait Primary</li>
                    <li>Portrait Secondary</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p>This table shows the supported combinations of operating systems and browsers for the orientation attribute.</p>
                
                <table class="u-Report u-Report--staticBG u-Report--stretch dm-Report--doc dm-Report--grid col-8">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="display-hidden"></td>
                            <th class="u-tL">Chrome</th>
                            <th class="u-tL">Edge</th>
                            <th class="u-tL">Firefox</th>
                            <th class="u-tL">Safari</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <th class="u-tL" scope="row"><span>Android</span></th>
                            <td class="display-visible">Yes</td>
                            <td class="display-visible">Yes</td>
                            <td class="display-visible">Yes</td>
                            <td class="display-hidden">N/A</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th class="u-tL" scope="row"><span>iOS</span></th>
